  "prompt": "What are the types of pain during pregnancy?",
  "response": "During pregnancy, women can experience various types of pain:\n\n1. Common Pain Types:\n- Back pain\n- Pelvic pain\n- Round ligament pain\n- Sciatica\n- Leg cramps\n- Headaches\n- Breast tenderness\n\n2. Lower Back Pain\n- Caused by hormonal changes\n- Weight gain\n- Postural shifts\n- Weakened abdominal muscles\n\n3. Pelvic Pain\n- Symphysis pubis dysfunction\n- Pelvic girdle pain\n- Joint relaxation\n- Increased hormone relaxin\n\n4. Abdominal Pain\n- Stretching of uterus\n- Gas and constipation\n- Braxton Hicks contractions\n- Round ligament pain\n\n5. Joint and Muscle Pain\n- Increased body weight\n- Hormonal changes\n- Relaxed ligaments\n- Pressure on joints\n\n6. Potential Serious Pain Indicators\n- Sharp abdominal pain\n- Persistent headaches\n- Sudden swelling\n- Severe back pain\n- Bleeding\n\n7. Trimester-Specific Pain\n- First trimester: Implantation cramps\n- Second trimester: Round ligament pain\n- Third trimester: Braxton Hicks, labor contractions\n\nAlways consult healthcare professionals about persistent or severe pain.",
